analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all randomized subjects who received at least one dose of study drug.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Full Analysis Set (FAS) includes all randomized subjects who received at least one dose of study drug.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >= 1 dose of study drug

analysisPopulations.name: Per Protocol Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Per Protocol Analysis Set represents a subset of the FAS and consists of all FAS subjects who did not have any major protocol deviations that are determined to have a potential impact on the primary efficacy endpoint up to Week 12 in Period 1 of the study.
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Per Protocol Analysis Set represents a subset of the FAS and consists of all FAS subjects who did not have any major protocol deviations that are determined to have a potential impact on the primary efficacy endpoint up to Week 12 in Period 1 of the study.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Included in FAS AND no major protocol deviations impacting primary efficacy endpoint through Week 12

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Analysis Set consists of all subjects who received at least one dose of study drug. For the Safety Analysis Set, subjects will be analyzed "as treated," regardless of the treatment randomized.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Analysis Set consists of all subjects who received at least one dose of study drug. For the Safety Analysis Set, subjects will be analyzed "as treated," regardless of the treatment randomized.
